WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.000
Today I'm going to talk about my latest project, the Dashboard-Builder, or how to build Shiny

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:13.560
Apps without writing code.

00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:17.719
And now, quick disclaimer, this is not the UI-Builder.

00:00:17.719 --> 00:00:21.840
So yesterday at the keynote, it was a bit of an emotional rollercoaster for me, because

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:25.719
I saw, oh, you guys are doing a UI-Builder, I'm doing a Dashboard-Builder, okay.

00:00:25.719 --> 00:00:29.160
I'm just going to see myself out, okay, nothing to do here.

00:00:29.160 --> 00:00:31.959
But I think it's still a bit different.

00:00:31.959 --> 00:00:35.439
So if I'm not from RStudio, then who am I?

00:00:35.439 --> 00:00:37.080
Well, I'm Peter.

00:00:37.080 --> 00:00:42.040
I just finished my master's in data engineering and analytics from the Technical University

00:00:42.040 --> 00:00:43.880
in Munich.

00:00:43.880 --> 00:00:49.320
And in my free time, I like to play chess and do data visualizations, especially Shiny

00:00:49.320 --> 00:00:50.320
dashboards.

00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:56.240
Now, when I talk to people and tell them about my hobbies, well, most call me a nerd, but

00:00:56.320 --> 00:01:01.320
there are also a few people who say, oh, visualizations, dashboards, I would like to

00:01:01.320 --> 00:01:06.400
create more dashboards, but I don't know how.

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:08.160
I can't write R code.

00:01:08.160 --> 00:01:09.800
It's too complex.

00:01:09.800 --> 00:01:14.639
And then there are some people who say I could do it, I know how to do it, but I have so

00:01:14.639 --> 00:01:18.919
many great ideas, I just don't have enough time.

00:01:18.919 --> 00:01:21.160
And I think these are all valid reasons.

00:01:21.160 --> 00:01:25.360
But I'm here, I want to tell you to create more dashboards.

00:01:25.480 --> 00:01:31.720
So more dashboards like this one I created about my recent chess games.

00:01:31.720 --> 00:01:36.040
Is this the most sophisticated, the most beautiful dashboard you've ever seen?

00:01:36.040 --> 00:01:37.040
Probably not.

00:01:37.040 --> 00:01:38.040
I hope not.

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:42.959
If it is, go check out the Shiny gallery, go check out some Shiny contests.

00:01:42.959 --> 00:01:46.180
But I still think that that's a decent dashboard.

00:01:46.180 --> 00:01:53.279
And everyone in this room can build this dashboard without writing R code, without prior knowledge

00:01:53.279 --> 00:01:59.800
of Shiny, and you can do it in two minutes and 22 seconds.

00:01:59.800 --> 00:02:00.800
I know.

00:02:00.800 --> 00:02:02.760
But I can prove it to you.

00:02:02.760 --> 00:02:04.279
I have a video.

00:02:04.279 --> 00:02:07.500
And you can see the time on the bottom right.

00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:11.619
So if you open up the dashboard builder, you're greeted with a blank screen.

00:02:11.619 --> 00:02:14.820
And if you want to visualize data, well, you need data.

00:02:14.820 --> 00:02:19.839
So I downloaded some of my chess games, saved it as a CSV file, and then I'm just loading

00:02:19.839 --> 00:02:22.539
it into the dashboard builder.

00:02:22.539 --> 00:02:28.440
And then I can add elements like a table about the date and the results of my game.

00:02:28.440 --> 00:02:31.619
And then I'm adding a graph about my rating points.

00:02:31.619 --> 00:02:34.979
So in chess, if you win games, you gain rating points.

00:02:34.979 --> 00:02:36.740
If you lose, you lose rating points.

00:02:36.740 --> 00:02:38.720
So I can visualize this.

00:02:38.720 --> 00:02:43.100
I can add some value boxes about the number of games I've played.

00:02:43.100 --> 00:02:44.740
The number's too high.

00:02:44.740 --> 00:02:48.559
And my peak rating.

00:02:48.559 --> 00:02:50.899
And then I can add more elements.

00:02:50.899 --> 00:02:55.179
And if it's too small for you, if you can't see everything that's going on, that's fine.

00:02:55.179 --> 00:02:58.860
I just wanted you to take away how easy it is.

00:02:58.860 --> 00:03:00.419
You don't have to write any code.

00:03:00.419 --> 00:03:03.740
And trust me, it's also a lot of fun.

00:03:03.740 --> 00:03:09.860
And while I'm here creating the last couple of graphs, the next part is the interesting

00:03:09.860 --> 00:03:10.860
part.

00:03:10.860 --> 00:03:12.940
There's an export button up there.

00:03:12.940 --> 00:03:17.460
And once you click on export, the dashboard builder generates R code.

00:03:17.460 --> 00:03:22.660
It generates the R code that is needed to build this dashboard.

00:03:22.660 --> 00:03:25.020
And then it downloads this.

00:03:25.020 --> 00:03:30.479
And then you can open it up in R studio.

00:03:30.479 --> 00:03:34.279
And then you open up the file.

00:03:34.279 --> 00:03:35.279
And once you hit run...

00:03:35.279 --> 00:03:44.779
And now, look, it looks exactly like the one we just created.

00:03:44.779 --> 00:03:45.779
Okay.

00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:49.940
So now you have a first impression what the dashboard builder can do.

00:03:49.940 --> 00:03:52.699
So I quickly want to say what it is not.

00:03:52.699 --> 00:03:55.740
So it's not a standalone tool.

00:03:55.740 --> 00:04:01.419
It's not Power BI, Tableau, or whatever in R. Why not?

00:04:01.419 --> 00:04:05.740
I think these tools are great, but there are certain soft locks.

00:04:05.740 --> 00:04:13.059
I think with every tool, you have the ease of use versus the extendability and power.

00:04:13.059 --> 00:04:15.619
Now, this part is highly opinionated.

00:04:16.459 --> 00:04:17.459
So please don't be angry.

00:04:17.459 --> 00:04:20.019
I think Power BI is easy to use.

00:04:20.019 --> 00:04:21.500
But it's not powerful.

00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:25.859
You can't do machine learning, deep learning, serious data science.

00:04:25.859 --> 00:04:29.459
If you want to do it, it's very hard.

00:04:29.459 --> 00:04:36.220
And then let's look at R. If you combine it with HTML, JavaScript, and CSS, it's super

00:04:36.220 --> 00:04:37.220
powerful.

00:04:37.220 --> 00:04:39.059
We all know what R can do.

00:04:39.059 --> 00:04:42.459
But I would argue it's not that easy to use.

00:04:42.459 --> 00:04:43.779
So what can we do?

00:04:44.739 --> 00:04:48.500
We can use R and Shiny, which is a bit easier to use.

00:04:48.500 --> 00:04:51.459
But I still think there's something up there.

00:04:51.459 --> 00:04:53.980
And I want to go up there.

00:04:53.980 --> 00:04:54.980
What's up there?

00:04:54.980 --> 00:04:59.859
Well, I think up there is a WYSIWYG dashboard builder.

00:04:59.859 --> 00:05:02.500
WYSIWYG means what you see is what you get.

00:05:02.500 --> 00:05:07.019
So if you have R Markdown, that's not WYSIWYG, because you have to build it.

00:05:07.019 --> 00:05:12.179
So if you want to increase the size of a picture in Markdown, you have to put in width 50%,

00:05:12.579 --> 00:05:15.540
width 70%, and then you build it, and then you can see, oh, it's too small.

00:05:15.540 --> 00:05:17.220
So you have to get back to the code.

00:05:17.220 --> 00:05:21.820
If you compare this to PowerPoint, which is WYSIWYG, if you want to increase the size

00:05:21.820 --> 00:05:25.179
of an image, you click on the image, and you scale it.

00:05:25.179 --> 00:05:26.720
And then that's how big it is.

00:05:26.720 --> 00:05:27.720
That's what you get.

00:05:27.720 --> 00:05:30.339
What you see is what you get.

00:05:30.339 --> 00:05:36.420
But I also want all the power and packages of R. I want the data science.

00:05:36.420 --> 00:05:37.820
I want the machine learning.

00:05:37.820 --> 00:05:40.260
I want the visualizations.

00:05:40.260 --> 00:05:44.859
So that's what I want, a combination of these.

00:05:44.859 --> 00:05:47.059
So why?

00:05:47.059 --> 00:05:48.059
What does it add?

00:05:48.059 --> 00:05:49.260
Who is it for?

00:05:49.260 --> 00:05:50.899
And I think there are two target groups.

00:05:50.899 --> 00:05:53.500
The first one, beginners.

00:05:53.500 --> 00:05:56.619
I don't think that only data scientists should create dashboards.

00:05:56.619 --> 00:05:58.279
There are other sciences.

00:05:58.279 --> 00:06:04.700
They have so much data, so much insight that they can use to create dashboards.

00:06:04.700 --> 00:06:08.640
But it has to be easy to use, because most of them don't know how to write code.

00:06:09.320 --> 00:06:14.160
I think the blank screen, when you start a project, that's really frightening.

00:06:14.160 --> 00:06:20.239
So if we can help them, first step, without them having to know how to program, I think

00:06:20.239 --> 00:06:25.040
that's going to lower the entry barrier to data visualization.

00:06:25.040 --> 00:06:26.760
And then there are the experts.

00:06:26.760 --> 00:06:31.760
But if you just go to a client, discuss how the dashboard will look like, that's never

00:06:31.760 --> 00:06:34.239
going to be how it will look like in the end.

00:06:34.239 --> 00:06:36.839
So you build the dashboard.

00:06:36.839 --> 00:06:37.839
Then you bring it to the client.

00:06:38.040 --> 00:06:39.799
It tells you, oh, can we change this?

00:06:39.799 --> 00:06:42.320
So you have to go back, change it, go to the client.

00:06:42.320 --> 00:06:43.320
Can we change this?

00:06:43.320 --> 00:06:44.320
No.

00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:49.239
I want you to be there in the room with a client or maybe just with your team and build

00:06:49.239 --> 00:06:52.260
rapid prototyping, build the dashboard.

00:06:52.260 --> 00:06:56.880
So we're going to streamline the dashboard building process so you have more time for

00:06:56.880 --> 00:07:00.000
the really interesting stuff.

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:04.320
So now you're wondering, how does it work?

00:07:04.320 --> 00:07:06.359
If you open it up, there are three buttons.

00:07:06.359 --> 00:07:09.239
And these three buttons are the three steps you have to take.

00:07:09.239 --> 00:07:10.239
You have to import data.

00:07:10.239 --> 00:07:12.440
Then you're going to build the dashboard.

00:07:12.440 --> 00:07:13.799
And then you export it.

00:07:13.799 --> 00:07:19.200
And then there's a fourth open ended step, improve and extend.

00:07:19.200 --> 00:07:22.239
So we're going to import data.

00:07:22.239 --> 00:07:25.279
We have this module up here.

00:07:25.279 --> 00:07:28.160
We can import data from our environment.

00:07:28.160 --> 00:07:31.440
We can load external files and Google Sheets.

00:07:31.440 --> 00:07:33.279
Now, I did not create this.

00:07:33.279 --> 00:07:39.320
I shamelessly stole it from the guys from Dreamers.

00:07:39.320 --> 00:07:43.839
And once you've loaded the data, you can start to build the dashboard.

00:07:43.839 --> 00:07:45.359
Now there are two steps.

00:07:45.359 --> 00:07:47.239
First you create the element.

00:07:47.239 --> 00:07:53.320
Right now we support text boxes, value boxes, data tables, and graphs.

00:07:53.320 --> 00:07:58.239
So for text boxes, just put in the text you want to be displayed.

00:07:58.279 --> 00:08:03.559
For value boxes, put in a title, a value, and then an icon.

00:08:03.559 --> 00:08:05.519
Data table, also very easy.

00:08:05.519 --> 00:08:09.600
Just select the columns you want to be displayed.

00:08:09.600 --> 00:08:16.040
But how are we going to create ggplots, graphs, without writing code?

00:08:16.040 --> 00:08:20.679
And thankfully, the guys from Dreamers have this awesome SKIS package.

00:08:20.679 --> 00:08:23.440
I'm sure most of you have seen it.

00:08:23.440 --> 00:08:28.799
You see up there in the top, those are all your columns from your data.

00:08:28.799 --> 00:08:35.400
And then you can drag and drop these columns to the X, the Y, maybe the color, whatever.

00:08:35.400 --> 00:08:39.799
And then it's going to create a graph for you.

00:08:39.799 --> 00:08:42.200
And then you have this element.

00:08:42.200 --> 00:08:46.359
And then you can edit the content.

00:08:46.359 --> 00:08:47.640
You can scale it.

00:08:47.640 --> 00:08:49.359
You can move it around.

00:08:49.359 --> 00:08:51.479
And you can also delete it.

00:08:51.479 --> 00:08:54.520
And then you're just going to repeat these two steps.

00:08:54.520 --> 00:09:02.219
So add an element, scale it, add an element, scale it, add more elements, move them around.

00:09:02.219 --> 00:09:05.200
And then you kind of build your dashboard.

00:09:05.200 --> 00:09:09.119
And as soon as you're happy with how it looks, export it.

00:09:09.119 --> 00:09:10.919
And when you export it, you get three files.

00:09:10.919 --> 00:09:13.000
You get the R project.

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:16.760
You get the data that you loaded in as a .rds file.

00:09:16.760 --> 00:09:19.159
And you get the app.r file.

00:09:19.159 --> 00:09:23.640
And in the app, there's always a UI and a server.

00:09:23.640 --> 00:09:27.359
And now let's look a bit deeper into the UI and the server files.

00:09:27.359 --> 00:09:28.359
Let's start with the UI.

00:09:28.359 --> 00:09:34.599
For these two elements, two value boxes, internally, we use the grid stacker package.

00:09:34.599 --> 00:09:40.640
So we just add a grid stack item, give it a height, a width, X, Y, give it some ID,

00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:41.640
some styling.

00:09:41.640 --> 00:09:45.719
And then in there, please give us a value box output.

00:09:45.719 --> 00:09:48.559
Now we're going to do the same for the second one.

00:09:48.559 --> 00:09:52.119
And if this looks a bit complicated, if it was too fast, don't worry.

00:09:52.119 --> 00:09:56.159
All of this is 100% generated by the dashboard builder.

00:09:56.159 --> 00:09:58.719
And we also have the same for the server.

00:09:58.719 --> 00:10:00.760
We're going to render a value box.

00:10:00.760 --> 00:10:01.760
Which value box?

00:10:01.760 --> 00:10:05.200
Well, just this title, Games Played.

00:10:05.200 --> 00:10:06.280
The value is 200.

00:10:06.280 --> 00:10:08.359
And then we have an icon and a width.

00:10:08.359 --> 00:10:09.900
And the same for the second one.

00:10:09.900 --> 00:10:13.400
And again, 100% generated.

00:10:13.400 --> 00:10:18.000
But now comes the part where I have to admit that I lied to you.

00:10:18.440 --> 00:10:20.760
You do have to write a tiny bit of code.

00:10:20.760 --> 00:10:24.719
Because look, the value boxes, the values, are hard-coded.

00:10:24.719 --> 00:10:28.799
So if the data changes, these values will stay the same.

00:10:28.799 --> 00:10:33.799
And that brings us to the fourth and final step, to improve and extend.

00:10:33.799 --> 00:10:38.280
Now that you have your dashboard, you can do so much with it.

00:10:38.280 --> 00:10:42.520
And in our case, let's see, okay, Games Played.

00:10:42.520 --> 00:10:45.739
That's just the number of rows of my data table.

00:10:45.739 --> 00:10:49.900
And the highest rating, well, the highest rating is just the max of my rating.

00:10:49.900 --> 00:10:53.739
So you have to write these two tiny lines of code.

00:10:53.739 --> 00:10:58.900
And I think most of us, most of you, all of you, all of you can do that.

00:10:58.900 --> 00:11:04.739
And then when you've done that, you get your dashboard.

00:11:04.739 --> 00:11:06.820
Now I know what you all want to do.

00:11:06.820 --> 00:11:08.619
You want to use the dashboard builder.

00:11:08.619 --> 00:11:11.260
It's still in alpha, but it works.

00:11:11.260 --> 00:11:14.099
So you can get a demo on Shiny apps.

00:11:14.099 --> 00:11:15.580
You can go to my GitHub.

00:11:15.580 --> 00:11:18.820
That will bring you to my GitHub.

00:11:18.820 --> 00:11:24.900
But you need for both, for the GitHub, if you want to run it locally, and if you want

00:11:24.900 --> 00:11:29.099
to run the apps that you created, you need the Grid Circle package.

00:11:29.099 --> 00:11:31.460
And you can download this from GitHub.

00:11:31.460 --> 00:11:35.419
I'm going to put it on Cron, but right now, you still have to do the DevTools install

00:11:35.419 --> 00:11:37.700
GitHub.

00:11:37.700 --> 00:11:41.260
And then how can we all improve the dashboard builder?

00:11:41.419 --> 00:11:46.419
Well, I was a bit busy the last two months because I had to finish my master's thesis.

00:11:46.419 --> 00:11:48.859
But now I have some free time.

00:11:48.859 --> 00:11:50.380
I'm just job hunting.

00:11:50.380 --> 00:11:52.020
And I want to improve the dashboard builder.

00:11:52.020 --> 00:11:56.299
So please, if you have feedback, if you have ideas, if you have questions, write me an

00:11:56.299 --> 00:12:00.500
email, open up an issue on GitHub, or just ask me right now.

00:12:00.500 --> 00:12:01.500
Thank you.

00:12:01.739 --> 00:12:02.739
Thank you.

00:12:02.739 --> 00:12:03.739
Thank you.

00:12:03.739 --> 00:12:03.739


